data.content:
Your code **doesn't use `Thread.Abort`**, `Thread.Interrupt`, or catch `ThreadAbortException`. It only uses `Thread.Start()`, `Thread.Join()`, and `Thread.Sleep()` — all of which work identically in .NET 8 with no migration needed.

That said, the code would benefit from modernization using `Task` / `Parallel.ForEach` instead of raw threads:

```csharp
public class SimpleWorker
{
    public void RunBatch(List<WorkItem> items)
    {
        Parallel.ForEach(items, item =>
        {
            Thread.Sleep(100);
            item.Result = ComputeResult(item.Input);
        });
    }
}
```

This gives you thread-pool efficiency and simpler code, but it's **optional** — your current code will compile and run correctly on .NET 8 as-is.
